**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Client-side JavaScript can be disabled, modified, or bypassed entirely
- API endpoints are directly accessible via curl, Postman, or automated scripts
- Attackers can enumerate resources by incrementing IDs (IDOR)
- Sensitive data like password hashes and SSNs are exposed to any caller
